%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20study%2C%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fsciadv.adg9817%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScience%20Advances%3C%2Fa%3E%20Wednesday%2C%20may%20provide%20some%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrat%20and%20his%20co-authors%20drew%20from%20a%20database%20of%204%2C000%20human%20genomes%20extracted%20from%20human%20remains%20dating%20back%20up%20to%2040%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20held%20by%20the%20Harvard%20Medical%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20study%20found%20that%20up%20to%20about%2020%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20European%20genomes%20were%20indeed%20richer%20in%20Neanderthal%20DNA%20than%20the%20Asian%20genomes%20they%20have%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20proportion%20shifted%20about%205%2C000%20to%2010%2C000%20years%20ago.%20What%20the%20scientists%20think%20happened%20then%20is%20that%20a%20group%20of%20farming%20Homo%20sapiens%20from%20Anatolia%2C%20now%20Western%20Turkey%2C%20started%20mixing%20with%20hunter-gatherers%20in%20Western%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20farmers%20had%20a%20little%20less%20Neanderthal%20in%20them%2C%20so%20Western%20Europeans%20lost%20some%20of%20that%20ancestry%20as%20they%20mixed%2C%20Currat%20said%2C%20per%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20not%20quite%20clear%2C%20however%2C%20is%20what%20happened%20in%20Asia.%20That's%20in%20part%20because%20the%20database%20the%20scientists%20were%20looking%20at%20had%20a%20lot%20less%20information%20about%20Asian%20genomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20turns%20out%20that%20archaeological%20excavations%20have%20been%20much%20more%20numerous%20in%20Europe%2C%20which%20greatly%20facilitates%20the%20study%20of%20the%20genomes%20of%20European%20populations%2C''%20said%20study%20author%20Claudio%20Quilodr%C3%A1n%2C%20a%20geneticist%20at%20the%20UNIGE%20Faculty%20of%20Science%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurek