rces%20from%20the%20country.%20Or%20pro-Iranian%20groups%20in%20countries%20such%20as%20Iraq%2C%20Syria%2C%20and%20Yemen%20could%20attempt%20to%20attack%20US%20sites%20in%20the%20region%20such%20as%20military%20bases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20would%20find%20it%20difficult%20to%20strike%20Israel%20directly%2C%26quot%3B%20Clive%20Jones%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20Israel%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%20at%20Durham%20University%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.france24.com%2Fen%2Fmiddle-east%2F20231013-from-gaza-to-lebanon-israel-faces-threats-on-multiple-fronts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20AFP%20news%20wire.%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BBut%20they%20could%20attack%20American%20interests%20in%20the%20region.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiMino%2C%20the%20former%20CIA%20analyst%2C%20told%20The%20Responsible%20Statecraft%20blog%2C%20that%20such%20an%20escalation%20could%20lead%20to%20pressure%20from%20Israel%20for%20the%20US%20to%20strike%20Iran%20itself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20that%20would%20be%20a%20disaster%20for%20all%20parties%20involved%2C%20not%20least%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20DiMino%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20that%20this%20administration%20wants%20to%20do%20that%2C%20but%20I%20do%20think%20once%20these%20events%20start%20to%20roll%20together%20and%20the%20decision%20matrices%20and%20the%20timelines%20that%20those%20decisions%20have%20to%20be%20made%20on%20get%20narrower%20and%20narrower%2C%20that%20these%20kinds%20of%20things%20can%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-hamas-war-will-hezbollah-draw-us-troops-broader-conflict-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697710495000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652fb36b211def8ed837e170%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bus