hers-spend-on-basic-school-supplies-2019-8%5C%22%3Eteacher%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20York%2C%20has%20bought%20learning%20worksheets%20and%20activities%2C%20multiple%20bins%20for%20her%20classroom%20library%2C%20flashlights%20for%20reading%20time%2C%20and%20her%20computer%20chair%20for%20her%20classroom%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20The%20money%20for%20those%20purchases%20largely%20came%20out%20of%20her%20own%20pocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20documentation%20shared%20with%20Insider%2C%20Nicole%20had%20spent%20a%20minimum%20of%20%244%2C000%20of%20her%20own%20money%20on%20classroom%20materials%20and%20supplies%20since%202019.%20She%20has%20spent%20at%20least%20%24400%20this%20year%20on%20things%20like%20a%20letter%20tray%2C%20worksheets%2C%20and%20bulletin%20board%20kits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20first%20start%2C%20you%20have%20desks%2C%20you%20have%20chairs%2C%20and%20maybe%20a%20couple%20bookshelves%2C%20and%20that's%20really%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicole%2C%20who%20began%20to%20teach%20in%202019%20after%20being%20a%20substitute%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole's%20last%20name%20is%20known%20to%20Insider%20but%20withheld%20for%20privacy%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20is%20not%20alone%20in%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fteachers-are-spending-their-own-money-on-their-classrooms-2018-11%5C%22%3Eout-of-pocket%20purchases%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fteacher-spent-2000-dollars-own-money-classroom-supplies-2022-8%5C%22%3Eteachers%20spend%20their%20own%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20supplies%20and%20teaching%20materials%20amid%20insufficient%20funding%20for%20those%20expenses.%20A%20teacher%20survey%20from%20AdoptAClassroom.org%20this%20year%20found%20the%20average%20out-of-pocket%20spending%20amount%20on%20supplies%20was%20%24860.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20average%20is%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20more%20than%20the%20median%20budget%20they%20said%20they%20got%20for%20this%20past%20school%20year.%20%26quot%3BTeachers%20said%20the%20median%20classroom%20school%20supply%20budget%20during%20the%202022-2023%20school%20year%20was%20%24200%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adoptaclassroom.org%2F2023%2F06%2F07%2Fdo-teachers-need-to-buy-their-own-supplies-in-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20about%20the%20results%20on%20AdoptAClassroom.org%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%20%26quot%3BAdditionally%2C%2047%25%20of%20teachers%20said%20their%20classroom%20budget%20does%20not%20go%20as%20far%20due%20to%20inflation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Nicole%20has%20spent%20thousands%20of%20her%20own%20money%20so%20far%2C%20she%20also%20has%20received%20donations%2C%20some%20money%20from%20the%20school%2C%20and%20a%20small%20reimbursement%20from%20the%20school's%20PTA.%20Students%20also%20bring%20in%20school%20supplies%20they%20may%20need.%20She%20also%20makes%20videos%20about%20being%20a%20teacher%20on%20her%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40teachinglittlewonderz%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20she%20said%20she%20has%20received%20items%20for%20her%20classroom%20through%20company%20partnerships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20thinks%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20more%20investment%20into%20teachers'%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20ask%20other%20professions%20to%20try%20to%20do%20their%20job%20without%20the%20materials%20they%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20teachers%20are%20expected%20to%20do%20their%20job%20without%20materials%20that%20they%20have%20or%20that%20they%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20shopping%20cart%20filled%20with%20Target%20bags%20and%20things%20for%20a%20classroom.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652d87a56561dd877e7bafad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENicole's%20shopping%20cart%2C%20which%20includes%20bins%20for%20her%20classroom.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Nicole%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20for%20teachers%20is%20low%20pay%3A%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fpublication%2Fteacher-pay-in-2022%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Sylvia%20Allegretto%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Economic%20and%20Policy%20Research%20and%20a%20research%20associate%20at%20the%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute%2C%20found%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteacher-salary-pay-penalty-worse-wage-gap-report-2023-10%5C%22%3Epay%20penalty%20for%20teachers%20and%20comparable%20college%20graduates%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20are%20working%20was%20at%20a%20record%20large%20gap%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20a%20pay%20penalty%20of%2026.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLow%20pay%20makes%20recruiting%20and%20retaining%20highly%20qualified%20teachers%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20Allegretto%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BA%20lack%20of%20well-qualified%20teachers%20means%20we%20cannot%20equip%20future%20tech%20innovators%2C%20researchers%2C%20and%20educators%20with%20the%20training%20they%20need%20to%20emerge%20as%20leaders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20said%20that%20the%20purchases%20she%20made%20were%20needed%20%C2%A0%26quot%3Bto%20make%20my%20students%20interested%20and%20engaged%20and%20making%20them%20feel%20like%20they're%20in%20a%20warm%2C%20safe%20environment%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20given%20how%20much%20time%20is%20spent%20a%20day%20and%20across%20an%20entire%20school%20year%20in%20the%20same%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20in%20a%20room%20that's%20just%20four%20walls%20and%20chairs%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicole%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20going%20to%20motivate%20them%20or%20make%20them%20feel%20ex