er%20long-term%20initiatives%20that%20make%20up%20a%20sustainable%20health%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20Israeli%20occupation%20from%201967%2C%20several%20Palestinian%20hospitals%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Funispal%2Fdocument%2Fauto-insert-201580%2F%5C%22%3Eturned%20into%20detention%20centers%20or%20military%20offices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20others%20were%20closed%2C%20and%20new%20ones%20were%20prohibited%20from%20opening.%20Palestinian%20physicians%20working%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories%20earned%20one-third%20the%20salary%20of%20their%20Israeli%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20this%20neglect%2C%20health%20indicators%20throughout%20what%20are%20now%20called%20the%20occupied%20territories%20%E2%80%93%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20Strip%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMaternal%20and%20infant%20mortality%20%E2%80%93%20typical%20indicators%20of%20health%20system%20functioning%20%E2%80%93%20tends%20to%20be%20high.%20For%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Funispal%2Fdocument%2Fauto-insert-201580%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20mid-1980s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20infant%20mortality%20was%20over%2030%20per%201%2C000%20live%20births%20for%20Palestinians%2C%20compared%20with%20just%20under%2010%20per%201%2C000%20among%20the%20Jewish%20population%20of%20Israel.%20And%20infant%20mortality%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2Finfant-mortality-gaza-no-longer-decline-%25E2%2580%259Calarming-trend%25E2%2580%259D-according-new%5C%22%3Eremained%20stubbornly%20high%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20a%20reliable%20drinkable%20water%20infrastructure%20and%20overall%20unsanitary%20conditions%20resulted%20in%20the%20spread%20of%20parasitic%20and%20other%20infectious%20diseases%2C%20like%20rotavirus%2C%20cholera%20and%20salmonella%20%E2%80%93%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.com%2Fmidd